<subSubSection id="F3E6652FC4771C2EFF28FAE6FAA9FEC4" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="BB4336A4C4771C2EFF28FAE6FAA9FEC4" blockId="32.[151,1437,150,825]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="8988EAB6C4771C2EFF28FAE6FEF7FF69" bold="true" box="[151,274,150,176]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Distinguished from all other known 
<taxonomicName id="7CFC4D27C4771C2EFD10FAE7FCA3FF68" box="[687,838,151,177]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Plectranthias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8988EAB6C4771C2EFD10FAE7FCA3FF68" box="[687,838,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Plectranthias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species in having the following combination of characters: dorsal rays X,15; fourth dorsal spine longest; pectoral rays 13, all unbranched; lateral line complete, with 29-30 scales; predorsal scales extend anteriorly only to middle of interorbital (above vertical through mid-pupil); at least some anterior scales with basal cteni; ventral edge of preopercle with two enlarged antrorse serrations.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F3E6652FC4771C2EFF78FB57FDF4FCE0" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="discussion">
